00:00:44,366 --> 00:00:46,244
Question is "where"?

14
00:00:47,869 --> 00:00:49,942
What? What are you trying
to tell me, Michael?

15
00:00:49,975 --> 00:00:53,883
I think I owe you an apology.
Because I lied to you.

16
00:00:54,997 --> 00:00:56,540
About Oscar Shales.

17
00:00:57,696 --> 00:01:01,771
Right there.
That's where I put the bullet in him.

18
00:01:03,445 --> 00:01:04,890
What are you doing, man?

19
00:01:05,728 --> 00:01:08,732
You've been hired to do a job.
The reasoning...

20
00:01:09,017 --> 00:01:10,562
does not concern you.

21
00:01:10,658 --> 00:01:12,163
You don't ask any
questions about us,

22
00:01:12,196 --> 00:01:15,080
maybe we'll continue to make sure no
one asks any questions about you.

23
00:01:15,115 --> 00:01:16,040
Are we clear?

24
00:01:17,896 --> 00:01:19,582
They all die.

25
00:01:53,396 --> 00:01:54,161
Hey.

26
00:01:55,278 --> 00:01:56,113
Hey.

27
00:01:56,526 --> 00:01:57,652
Are you new?

28
00:01:58,525 --> 00:01:59,650
Yeah.

29
00:02:00,157 --> 00:02:02,502
No one told me we were
getting a new volunteer.

30
00:02:02,967 --> 00:02:04,701
I've been working, uh,

31
00:02:04,985 --> 00:02:06,813
night shifts, cleanup and...

32
00:02:07,137 --> 00:02:10,050
Jimmy said I could
change my shift, so...

33
00:02:10,145 --> 00:02:12,160
You know what you're doin'?

34
00:02:12,585 --> 00:02:14,082
Yeah.

35
00:02:14,737 --> 00:02:17,122
- I'll see you around.
- Right.

36
00:03:17,008 --> 00:03:19,261
- This might be Scofield.
- Copy that.

37
00:03:53,128 --> 00:03:54,192
You take that side.

38
00:04:29,148 --> 00:04:31,491
- Freeze!
- Take it easy, man.

39
00:04:31,815 --> 00:04:34,060
- Stay on the ground.
- What's the deal?

40
00:04:34,998 --> 00:04:36,353
He's gone.

41
00:04:41,677 --> 00:04:42,983
How you feelin'?

42
00:04:43,445 --> 00:04:46,782
Okay, I guess. Tired.

43
00:04:48,957 --> 00:04:51,072
I'm a target, kid.

44
00:04:51,348 --> 00:04:53,411
As long as you're with me,
so are you.

45
00:04:53,645 --> 00:04:57,413
Things could get a lot worse before
they get better. You understand?

46
00:04:57,558 --> 00:05:00,103
But after we meet up with
Uncle Mike and get to Panama...

47
00:05:00,136 --> 00:05:02,731
Panama ain't a sure thing,
your uncle's plan is dangerous.

48
00:05:02,768 --> 00:05:06,511
I mean really
dangerous. Listen...

49
00:05:07,657 --> 00:05:10,001
all the charges against
you have been dropped;

50
00:05:10,147 --> 00:05:13,671
you're free and clear to
start a new life. A good life.

51
00:05:13,815 --> 00:05:16,171
Not be constantly running,
looking over your shoulder...

52
00:05:16,205 --> 00:05:19,262
You want me to leave?

53
00:05:20,098 --> 00:05:21,363
No.

54
00:05:24,507 --> 00:05:25,432
No.

55
00:05:25,946 --> 00:05:29,002
Good, 'cause I'm not.

56
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:37,242
Here you go.

57
00:05:40,387 --> 00:05:42,502
Turn the sound up
on the tube, Jenny.

58
00:05:42,876 --> 00:05:44,320
Beth Wilson, Chicago Gazette.

59
00:05:44,418 --> 00:05:47,430
Do you have any thoughts on
the death of David Apolskis?

60
00:05:47,848 --> 00:05:49,342
It was unfortunate.

61
00:05:50,407 --> 00:05:51,482
Oh, David.

62
00:05:51,718 --> 00:05:53,812
Was there any opportunity
to subdue him...

63
00:05:53,948 --> 00:05:55,791
Let me remind you
that despite his age,

64
00:05:55,826 --> 00:05:59,353
David "Tweener" Apolskis was a fugitive
who made a move for my weapon.

65
