I did not want to
have to kill him,

66
00:06:02,908 --> 00:06:05,833
but sometimes things happen that
are just out of your control.

67
00:06:05,868 --> 00:06:08,733
That good ole boy's huntin'
'em all down, ain't he?

68
00:06:08,965 --> 00:06:11,423
Mr. Mahone, sources claim that you've
recovered Scofield's hard drive

69
00:06:11,457 --> 00:06:13,342
and have obtained
substantial data from it.

70
00:06:13,378 --> 00:06:14,123
What sources?

71
00:06:14,268 --> 00:06:16,243
Allegedly you've retrieved
information detailing

72
00:06:16,278 --> 00:06:18,760
not only how Scofield broke out,
but how he plans to stay out.

73
00:06:18,798 --> 00:06:19,942
- Care to comment?
- No.

74
00:06:20,056 --> 00:06:22,273
The event at Blanding Botanical
Gardens earlier today,

75
00:06:22,307 --> 00:06:24,982
that was a result of
hard-drive data you collected.

76
00:06:25,546 --> 00:06:26,570
No comment.

77
00:06:27,358 --> 00:06:30,500
You found other locations where
Scofield might be headed? True?

78
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:32,333
I believe I said no comment.

79
00:06:32,475 --> 00:06:33,750
There's something
about this guy,

80
00:06:33,786 --> 00:06:36,473
it's like he knows where we're going,
what we're thinking.

81
00:06:36,506 --> 00:06:39,470
What role will the hard
drive play in your search?

82
00:06:43,597 --> 00:06:46,271
Heard it came back from the lab,
any findings?

83
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:49,000
Yeah, 3,200
nitroglycerine ampules.

84
00:06:49,146 --> 00:06:52,952
Scofield knew these needed to be
stored in a cool, moist area.

85
00:06:53,137 --> 00:06:56,162
Best place for that in the Utah
desert is the Botanical Gardens.

86
00:06:56,197 --> 00:06:58,120
- It's stable?
- All medical grade,

87
00:06:58,255 --> 00:07:01,830
safely used by heart patients all
the time. But in the aggregate...

88
00:07:01,977 --> 00:07:04,942
It could take out an entire building.
That box right there.

89
00:07:06,657 --> 00:07:08,850
This is why we can't have...

90
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:10,352
leaks...

91
00:07:10,776 --> 00:07:13,162
coming from this office.

92
00:07:14,047 --> 00:07:18,802
God help the agent who goes behind
my back and talks to the press.

93
00:07:27,495 --> 00:07:30,790
Can you elaborate on any of
your tactics in this manhunt?

94
00:07:31,765 --> 00:07:34,013
Sun Tzu said,
that if you know your enemy,

95
00:07:34,248 --> 00:07:36,702
you need not fear a hundred battles.
I know these men--

96
00:07:36,737 --> 00:07:39,631
who they are, where they came from,
where they want to go.

97
00:07:43,305 --> 00:07:47,592
These convicts are in
a constant battle.

98
00:07:48,518 --> 00:07:50,232
Not only with me,

99
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:52,710
but with themselves.

100
00:07:54,655 --> 00:07:57,332
Second guessing every
decision they make.

101
00:08:00,197 --> 00:08:01,692
Do I turn left?

102
00:08:02,767 --> 00:08:04,450
Do I turn right?

103
00:08:06,298 --> 00:08:08,131
Stay or go?

104
00:08:10,396 --> 00:08:14,212
My job is to know how they'll
answer these questions.

105
00:08:14,715 --> 00:08:17,913
The only way to win a war is to
try to know your prey completely

106
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:21,310
and then you get to go after your
enemy with everything you've got.

107
00:08:57,838 --> 00:09:00,373
Our half-priced
stuff is in the back.

108
00:09:00,975 --> 00:09:03,490
I'm looking for
something very specific.

109
00:09:03,686 --> 00:09:04,373
Okay.

110
00:09:09,048 --> 00:09:10,542
This is it.

111
00:09:11,658 --> 00:09:14,713
- This is exactly what I need.
- Great.

112
00:09:17,398 --> 00:09:21,022
We were just inches
away today, inches.

113
00:09:21,118 --> 00:09:24,280
I want these blown up, huge.
Put them in my office on the walls.

114
00:09:24,315 --> 00:09:26,062
- What are these?
- Somewhere in there is

115
00:09:26,098 --> 00:09:28,071
information regarding a
rendezvous that Scofield set up,

116
00:09:28,107 --> 00:09:29,863
and we're going to crack
that code today. Lang!

117
00:09:29,896 --> 00:09:31,811
Today's the day
Franklin told his wife

118
00:09:31,957 --> 00:09:33,752
he's going to meet her
at the Rainbow Room.

119
00:09:33,788 --> 00:09:34,031
That's right.

120
00:09:34,068 --> 00:09:36,993
Wrong. Today's the day Franklin's
going down. Are you ready?

121
00:09:37,025 --> 00:09:38,120
Everything's arranged.

122
00:09:58,026 --> 00:09:59,752
- It's all here?
- Yeah.

123
00:10:06,135 --> 00:10:08,771
Hey, yo, D. Wassup, baby?

124
00:10:09,697 --> 00:10:12,701
- I know that ain't you.
- Ain't a ghost, man.

125
00:10:13,355 --> 00:10:14,853
You holding up all right?

126
00:10:15,038 --> 00:10:18,212
Yeah. Just catching a whole bunch of
buses just to get here to Chi-town, man.

127
00:10:18,246 --> 00:10:20,220
How you think I'm
supposed to feel?

128
00:10:20,826 --> 00:10:25,100
Chris. Jay. Wassup, Flam?
You look like you lost a few, bro.

129
00:10:25,295 --> 00:10:27,502
- Slim-Fast, baby.
- Is that what it is, huh?

130
00:10:27,637 --> 00:10:29,951
The Feds been in your old
lady's business, no joke.

131
00:10:29,988 --> 00:10:32,580
Up in your crib,
and following her around sometimes.

132
00:10:32,807 --> 00:10:34,113
Yeah, I know, man. I know.

133
00:10:34,405 --> 00:10:35,752
Yo, I know you love Kacee,

134
00:10:35,935 --> 00:10:38,202
but I don't know if it's a good idea
for you to be coming around here.

135
00:10:38,237 --> 00:10:39,591
You're a wanted man.

136
00:10:39,736 --> 00:10:41,752
I'm wanted because I
kept my mouth shut,

137
00:10:41,898 --> 00:10:43,491
and I kept you
out of Fox River.

138
00:10:43,577 --> 00:10:45,720
See, man, we feel that,
and we owe you one.

139
00:10:46,056 --> 00:10:49,113
Good, 'cause I'm
collecting right now.

140
00:10:49,446 --> 00:10:51,173
My wife is waiting
for me today,

141
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:54,562
and I am not leaving Chi-town
without my family. You understand?

142
00:10:54,607 --> 00:10:57,383
Now, y'all going to help me.
Let's roll out.

143
00:11:11,486 --> 00:11:12,700
Where you going?

144
00:11:14,873 --> 00:11:17,220
Take my kid to school.

145
00:11:17,911 --> 00:11:19,658
I know about the Rainbow Room.

146
00:11:19,796 --> 00:11:21,214
I don't know what
you're talking about.

147
00:11:21,249 --> 00:11:22,413
Phone lines are tapped.

148
00:11:22,597 --> 00:11:25,333
We heard your entire telephone
conversation with your husband.

149
00:11:25,367 --> 00:11:27,921
And, since you and Dede aren't
booked on any flights to New York,

150
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:30,910
don't tell me the Rainbow Room
is a restaurant in Manhattan.

151
00:11:30,946 --> 00:11:33,312
Now, you can tell me where
you're meeting your husband,

152
00:11:33,348 --> 00:11:36,802
or I can arrest you right
in front of your daughter.

153
00:11:37,737 --> 00:11:39,180
You go to hell.

154
00:11:39,327 --> 00:11:41,050
I haven't done anything wrong.

155
00:11:43,097 --> 00:11:46,150
You spoke with an escaped
felon about meeting him today.

156
00:11:46,297 --> 00:11:49,120
You've already done enough to be
charged with attempt to aid and abet.

157
00:11:49,157 --> 00:11:51,450
Please, okay? Listen to me.

158
00:11:51,598 --> 00:11:54,043
One phone call and
Child Welfare is here,

159
00:11:54,175 --> 00:11:56,680
and you're going to County and
Dede will be in foster care.

160
00:11:56,715 --> 00:11:57,881
- No.
- Don't worry.

161
00:11:58,028 --> 00:12:01,273
I hear the families in the
foster system are top-notch.

162
00:12:05,118 --> 00:12:10,863
You are asking me to choose
between my daughter and my husband.

163
00:12:11,465 --> 00:12:12,770
Exactly.

164
00:12:14,297 --> 00:12:15,350
Anything?

165
00:12:15,536 --> 00:12:18,382
I'm on the phone with Fox River.
Checking Bagwell's file.

166
00:12:18,916 --> 00:12:20,740
Hey, what you got for me?

167
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:23,382
Really?

168
00:12:24,215 --> 00:12:25,561
52 times?

169
00:12:26,767 --> 00:12:27,932
Where?

170
00:12:30,705 --> 00:12:32,393
I owe you, Patterson.

171
00:12:34,387 --> 00:12:36,100
We got a lot of road to cover.

172
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:57,383
We're good?

173
00:13:04,415 --> 00:13:07,371
No more stops until
we get to New Mexico.

174
00:13:09,277 --> 00:13:12,181
- You forgot your change.
- Yeah, thanks.

175
00:13:12,376 --> 00:13:14,862
- You were in such a rush.
- Thanks.

176
00:13:18,058 --> 00:13:19,461
Keep walking.

177
00:13:19,695 --> 00:13:21,231
Keep walking.

178
00:13:21,708 --> 00:13:23,432
Come on, keep walking.

179
00:13:26,956 --> 00:13:28,350
Damn it.

180
00:13:38,116 --> 00:13:40,761
You don't have to ditch the car.
We can keep driving.

181
00:13:40,815 --> 00:13:44,111
Can't. The waitress made me and the car.
It's useless.

182
00:13:45,508 --> 00:13:48,043
Sorry, you know.
Maybe we can find another car.

183
00:13:48,457 --> 00:13:50,703
Cars ain't exactly
growing on trees out here.

184
00:13:50,708 --> 00:13:53,161
We've got 400 miles to go
and no way of getting there.

185
00:13:53,196 --> 00:13:56,272
We don't get to Michael in time,
he's going to leave without us.

186
00:13:56,306 --> 00:13:57,851
Uncle Mike wouldn't do that.

187
00:13:58,036 --> 00:14:00,821
He doesn't have a choice.
It's a one-shot deal out of the country.

188
00:14:00,855 --> 00:14:02,643
I said I was sorry.

189
00:14:03,655 --> 00:14:05,870
There was a sign back
there for a train station.

190
00:14:05,905 --> 00:14:07,420
- It ain't that easy.
- We'll follow the road...

191
00:14:07,457 --> 00:14:09,451
- It ain't that easy.
- We won't be seen.

192
00:14:10,046 --> 00:14:12,020
Hey, I'm not an idiot.

193
00:14:12,207 --> 00:14:14,361
I was on the run,
too, you know.

194
00:14:15,938 --> 00:14:19,752
Yeah, you were on the
run and you got caught.

195
00:14:20,127 --> 00:14:23,890
Yeah, well, I'm sorry I'm not a
pro at being a con like you, Dad.

196
00:14:24,008 --> 00:14:27,541
Maybe I should have just left
when you gave me the out, huh?

197
00:14:27,676 --> 00:14:30,292
- It's not like you care.
- Whoa, whoa.

198
00:14:30,435 --> 00:14:31,513
Take it easy.

199
00:14:33,268 --> 00:14:35,473
I'm sorry, all right?

200
00:14:43,527 --> 00:14:45,440
Sorry, I'm just...

201
00:14:48,128 --> 00:14:50,141
Let's get out of here.

202
00:15:00,785 --> 00:15:03,890
Mrs., uh, Mrs. Pamela Mahone?

203
00:15:04,025 --> 00:15:06,421
- Yes?
- I'm Agent Wayne Merrick, FBI.

204
00:15:06,865 --> 00:15:09,221
I'd like to talk to
you about your husband.

205
00:15:14,957 --> 00:15:16,920
I'm surprised...

206
00:15:17,158 --> 00:15:19,730
that you're coming to me for
a background check on Alex.

207
00:15:19,765 --> 00:15:20,980
It's standard procedure.

208
00:15:21,127 --> 00:15:24,242
We run these kind of checks when an
agent is about to be promoted to a,

209
00:15:24,277 --> 00:15:25,822
to a higher security clearance.

210
00:15:25,865 --> 00:15:28,652
No, I know that. I did this dance
the last time he was promoted.

211
00:15:28,687 --> 00:15:30,880
I just figured that
since we were divorced--

212
00:15:30,885 --> 00:15:34,380
I mean, I rarely speak to him and I
certainly don't follow his career.

213
00:15:34,555 --> 00:15:37,211
I really need to get this done tod,
so, uh,

214
00:15:37,445 --> 00:15:39,642
I promise I won't take
up much of your time.

215
00:15:40,165 --> 00:15:44,253
I' given enough time to my ex-husband,
Mr. Merrick.

216
00:15:44,356 --> 00:15:46,930
I see. The, uh...

217
